---
import Header from "../../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
import { siteConfig } from "../../config";
import "../../styles/global.css";

// üîÅ AMKOR PAGE CONFIG
const projectName = "Manufacturing/Product Ops Copilot for Profitability and Utilization";
const projectTagline =
  "A private, on prem LLM workflow that turns factory signals into a structured SITREP and an executive ready slide outline.";
const projectSummary =
  "Prototype case study for Amkor Tempe focused on faster triage, clearer decisions, and privacy preserving analytics for utilization and profitability.";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <title>{projectName} | {siteConfig.name}</title>
    <meta name="description" content={projectSummary} />
  </head>

  <body class="bg-background text-foreground">
    <Header />

    <main class="pt-24 pb-16">
      <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 space-y-10">
        {/* Top header */}
        <header class="space-y-3">
          <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-blue-500">Project</p>
          <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-100">{projectName}</h1>
          <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-gray-400">{projectTagline}</p>
          <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-gray-400">{projectSummary}</p>

          <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 space-y-2">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 font-semibold">Context</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
              Built as a fast prototype after speaking with Erin Martin (HR) and Drake Miller (Process Team) at the ASU career fair.
              The intent is to demonstrate an intern deliverable aligned to Amkor product engineering needs for analytics, utilization,
              and profitability workflows using LLM tools.
            </p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">
              This page is public but unlisted. It is intended for Amkor reviewers and interview discussion.
            </p>
          </div>
        </header>

        {/* WHY */}
        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-100">Why</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            Manufacturing and product teams often spend significant time converting scattered signals into decisions.
            Data exists, but the bottleneck is triage, interpretation, and communication. The result is slower response,
            more back and forth, and inconsistent reporting. This project proposes a private LLM driven workflow that turns
            operational signals into a structured SITREP and an executive ready slide outline in minutes.
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300">
            <li><span class="font-medium">Goal:</span> reduce time from signal to decision and improve clarity of recommendations.</li>
            <li><span class="font-medium">Goal:</span> standardize reporting so engineering managers can compare incidents week to week.</li>
            <li><span class="font-medium">Constraints:</span> data privacy, auditability, and messy real world logs.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        {/* WHAT */}
        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-100">What</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            A Manufacturing and Product Ops Copilot that ingests operational metrics and event logs, computes a small set of
            decision oriented KPIs, then uses a local LLM to generate two outputs:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300">
            <li><span class="font-medium">Downtime triage SITREP:</span> what happened, impact, likely drivers, and recommended actions.</li>
            <li><span class="font-medium">Slide outline:</span> a concise executive ready structure that can be pasted into PowerPoint.</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-100">Key requirements</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300">
            <li><span class="font-medium">Privacy first:</span> runs in a private environment with no external data egress by default.</li>
            <li><span class="font-medium">Actionable outputs:</span> recommendations tied to utilization and profitability impacts.</li>
            <li><span class="font-medium">Explainability:</span> every recommendation includes supporting evidence and data gaps.</li>
            <li><span class="font-medium">Fast iteration:</span> outputs must be generated quickly enough to be used daily or weekly.</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 space-y-3">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 font-semibold">What I expect Amkor will care about most</p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300">
              <li><span class="font-medium">Downtime triage:</span> faster, consistent SITREPs and next steps.</li>
              <li><span class="font-medium">Utilization:</span> knowing where capacity is constrained and why.</li>
              <li><span class="font-medium">Profitability:</span> translating yield, scrap, rework, and downtime into cost impact.</li>
              <li><span class="font-medium">Communication:</span> executive quality summaries that reduce meeting time.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        {/* SCHEMATIC & PLAN */}
        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-100">Schematic &amp; Plan</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            The architecture is intentionally simple for reliability and privacy. A data layer produces a small set of KPIs.
            A local LLM generates structured outputs. A UI presents the SITREP, key charts, and a one click slide outline.
          </p>

          <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/60 p-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-3">High level architecture diagram</p>

            <div class="w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-950/40">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 1200 420" role="img" aria-label="Ops Copilot architecture diagram" class="w-full h-auto">
                <defs>
                  <style>
                    .box { fill: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.6); stroke: rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.35); stroke-width: 2; rx: 18; }
                    .txt { fill: rgba(226, 232, 240, 0.95); font: 18px ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, Segoe UI, Roboto; }
                    .sub { fill: rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.95); font: 14px ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, Segoe UI, Roboto; }
                    .arrow { stroke: rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.85); stroke-width: 3; marker-end: url(#m); }
                  </style>
                  <marker id="m" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="8" refY="5" markerWidth="7" markerHeight="7" orient="auto-start-reverse">
                    <path d="M 0 0 L 10 5 L 0 10 z" fill="rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.85)"></path>
                  </marker>
                </defs>

                {/* Boxes */}
                <rect class="box" x="40" y="60" width="300" height="130" />
                <text class="txt" x="70" y="100">Factory signals</text>
                <text class="sub" x="70" y="130">events, alarms, downtime</text>
                <text class="sub" x="70" y="155">yield, scrap, rework</text>
                <text class="sub" x="70" y="180">throughput, utilization</text>

                <rect class="box" x="420" y="60" width="330" height="130" />
                <text class="txt" x="450" y="100">Metrics layer</text>
                <text class="sub" x="450" y="130">KPI rollups and features</text>
                <text class="sub" x="450" y="155">profitability and capacity impact</text>
                <text class="sub" x="450" y="180">data quality checks</text>

                <rect class="box" x="820" y="60" width="340" height="130" />
                <text class="txt" x="850" y="100">Local LLM engine</text>
                <text class="sub" x="850" y="130">private inference, no egress</text>
                <text class="sub" x="850" y="155">structured SITREP generation</text>
                <text class="sub" x="850" y="180">slide outline generation</text>

                <rect class="box" x="220" y="240" width="360" height="140" />
                <text class="txt" x="250" y="280">UI and reporting</text>
                <text class="sub" x="250" y="310">incident list, charts, SITREP</text>
                <text class="sub" x="250" y="335">evidence and confidence</text>
                <text class="sub" x="250" y="360">copy to PowerPoint</text>

                <rect class="box" x="660" y="240" width="500" height="140" />
                <text class="txt" x="690" y="280">Optional stretch</text>
                <text class="sub" x="690" y="310">policy gated redaction and escalation</text>
                <text class="sub" x="690" y="335">only if approved, only if sanitized</text>
                <text class="sub" x="690" y="360">external model never sees raw identifiers</text>

                {/* Arrows */}
                <line class="arrow" x1="340" y1="125" x2="420" y2="125" />
                <line class="arrow" x1="750" y1="125" x2="820" y2="125" />
                <line class="arrow" x1="990" y1="190" x2="450" y2="240" />
                <line class="arrow" x1="580" y1="310" x2="660" y2="310" />
              </svg>
            </div>

            <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-3">
              The default path is local only. The optional stretch path is a gated redaction plus escalation pattern, not the core.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        {/* COMPONENT SELECTION */}
        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-100">Component Selection</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            This is a prototype plan intended to map directly to the internship posting. Tool choices will be finalized during
            implementation based on Amkor internal constraints. The emphasis is on privacy, traceability, and outputs that teams will actually use.
          </p>

          <div class="space-y-3">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-100">Planned components</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300">
              <li>
                <span class="font-medium">Local LLM runtime</span> ‚Äî private inference on a local workstation or internal server.
              </li>
              <li>
                <span class="font-medium">Metrics and feature layer</span> ‚Äî small set of KPIs for utilization and profitability impact.
              </li>
              <li>
                <span class="font-medium">Reporting outputs</span> ‚Äî structured SITREP template plus PowerPoint ready slide outline.
              </li>
              <li>
                <span class="font-medium">Automation hooks</span> ‚Äî compatible with Copilot style workflows and Power Automate style triggers.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 space-y-2">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 font-semibold">Privacy and safety posture</p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300">
              <li>Default mode is local inference with no external data sharing.</li>
              <li>Outputs are designed to be auditable with referenced inputs and stated data gaps.</li>
              <li>Any external model use is a stretch concept behind explicit policy gating and redaction.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        {/* HOW */}
        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-100">How</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            The implementation plan is scoped to be completed quickly as a proof of capability. The objective is not a full production system.
            The objective is to demonstrate an intern deliverable that can be expanded inside Amkor with real data sources.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-100">Build plan</h3>
          <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300">
            <li>Define a realistic synthetic dataset schema for utilization, downtime, and profitability proxies.</li>
            <li>Compute KPI rollups and basic anomaly flags for incident selection.</li>
            <li>Generate a structured SITREP from selected incident data using a local LLM.</li>
            <li>Generate a slide outline output formatted for quick paste into PowerPoint.</li>
            <li>Build a clean UI that shows incident list, KPIs, SITREP, and slide outline.</li>
          </ol>

          <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 space-y-2">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
              Demo status
              <span class="text-gray-500"> (planned updates)</span>
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300">
              <li><span class="font-medium">Tonight:</span> publish case study page with architecture and requirements.</li>
              <li><span class="font-medium">This weekend:</span> implement a working prototype and record a short walkthrough.</li>
              <li><span class="font-medium">Next:</span> refine outputs for clearer utilization and profitability decision framing.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        {/* TESTING & RESULTS */}
        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-100">Testing &amp; Results</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            Results will be posted once the prototype is implemented. The evaluation metrics for the demo are intentionally practical:
            speed, clarity, and whether the recommendations are supported by visible evidence.
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300">
            <li><span class="font-medium">Time to SITREP:</span> generate a structured incident summary in under 60 seconds.</li>
            <li><span class="font-medium">Decision clarity:</span> outputs include recommended next actions and stated confidence.</li>
            <li><span class="font-medium">Presentation readiness:</span> slide outline can be pasted into PowerPoint with minimal editing.</li>
            <li><span class="font-medium">Privacy:</span> default operation requires no external data sharing.</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/60 p-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-3">Demo link (placeholder)</p>
            <div class="rounded-xl border border-dashed border-slate-700 p-4 text-sm text-slate-400">
              Add a YouTube link or embedded video here once recorded.
              <div class="mt-2 text-xs text-slate-500">
                Example: a 60 to 90 second walkthrough showing incident selection, SITREP output, and slide outline output.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        {/* NEXT STEPS */}
        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-100">What I&apos;d Do Next</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300">
            <li>Add evidence citations per recommendation, including which metrics triggered the conclusion.</li>
            <li>Add a confidence score and a ‚Äúmissing data‚Äù section to guide what to collect next.</li>
            <li>Add profitability and utilization decision templates for weekly review workflows.</li>
            <li>Integrate a simple automation trigger pattern compatible with Copilot and Power Automate style workflows.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        {/* Back link */}
        <div class="pt-4">
          <a
            href="/projects"
            class="text-sm text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 underline-offset-2 hover:underline"
          >
            ‚Üê Back to all projects
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>
